                            <p>ON THE EAST BASE OF THE LAKSHMĪNĀRĀYAṆA PERUMĀḶ TEMPLE.</p>						
                            <p>Parāntaka I. Year 38. 944-45 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription is dated in the 38th regnal year of <hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarman who conquered Madurai and Īḻam</hi> i.e., Parāntaka I.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This records the sale of land by the <hi rend="italic">Mūlaparaḍai (Mūlaparishad)</hi> of Mahēndramaṅgalam to Kāppiyaṉ Eḻuvaṉ-Gaṅgādharaṉ who endowed the same as <hi rend="italic">tiruviḷakkuppuṟam</hi> to god Tiruvagnīśvarattu-pperumāṉaḍigaḷ. The land was made tax-free by the <hi rend="italic">Mūlaparaḍai.</hi> The donor figures also in some more inscriptions from the place (vide Nos. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv17p0i0600">639</ref> above, <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv13p0i0002"><hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi> XIII, No. 2</ref>, No. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv17p0i0656A">656-A</ref>, below).</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
